COMMENTS="Installation
		1-) Download and install the extension ati-fglrx-kernel-source (ati license does not permit distribution of kernel module)
		2-) Run ati-fglrx-kernel-module-installer to build a kernel module extension which is required by ati-fglrx
			sudo ati-fglrx-kernel-module-installer
		3-) Download and install the extension ati-flgrx
		4-) Exit to prompt to terminate X and then run the following command:
			sudo aticonfig --initial
		5-) Start the desktop
			startx
		6-) For persistency you need to add etc/X11/xorg.conf to your backup list (/opt/.filetool.lst)
			echo \"etc/X11/xorg.conf\" >> /opt/.filetool.lst

		Important Notes for 64 bit kernel users:
		You need to load toolchain64 extension for building 64 bit kernel module, and
		run ati-fglrx-kernel-module-installer in a toolchain64 shell. You can start
		toolchain64 shell by executing toolchain64-shell in a standart terminal."
